    <section xml:id="installation">
        <title>Local installation</title>
        <subtitle>Quick Installation Guide using Docker</subtitle> 
        <para>Docker is an open-source container platform. Containers are lightweight, standalone packages that include everything needed to run an application.</para>
        <para>Using Docker, you can quickly run everything needed for TEI Publisher.</para>
        <section xml:id="prerequisites">
            <title>Requirements</title>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Docker ( 
                            <link xlink:href="https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/" xlink:show="new">Docker Desktop (Windows/Mac)</link>, 
                            <link xlink:href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/install" xlink:show="new">Docker Engine (Linux)</link> or
                            <link xlink:href="https://podman.io/docs/installation" xlink:show="new">Podman</link>
                        )
                    </para>                    
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>A modern web browser</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>If you do <emphasis role="bold">not</emphasis> want to use the Docker
                continue with <link xlink:href="installation.xml?id=exist-installation">installing
                    into an eXist instance</link>. Find more information on TEI Publisher and Docker
                    <link xlink:href="installation.xml?id=docker">here</link>. 
                    </para>
                    <note><para>When using the Docker image, you do <emphasis role="bold">not</emphasis> need
                    <link xlink:href="https://www.java.com/" xlink:show="new">Java</link> or <link xlink:href="https://exist-db.org/" xlink:show="new">eXist-db</link> installed
                locally.  </para></note>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="running">
            <title>Running TEI Publisher and Jinks</title>
            
            <para>
                <emphasis role="bold">
                    Please be aware that the TEI Publisher Dev Docker Container is not safe for use on public servers!
                    To run TEI Publisher on the server please make sure to read <link xlink:href="tldr.xml#production">Running TEI Publisher in Production</link> below.
                </emphasis>
            </para>
           
            
            <para>Make sure Docker is running and start TEI Publisher using the official pre-built
                Docker image by running the following command from your terminal: </para>
            <para>
            <programlisting>docker run -p 8080:8080 -v exist-data:/exist/data
                existdb/teipublisher:latest</programlisting>
            </para>
            <para>Point your browser to <link xlink:href="http://localhost:8080/exist/apps/tei-publisher/doc/tldr.xml" xlink:show="new">localhost:8080/exist/apps/tei-publisher/doc/tldr.xml</link> to verify everthing
                works fine. You should see this page but now served by the TEI Publisher Dev Docker
                Container you just started.</para>
            </section>
            <section xml:id="homepage">
            <title>TEI Publisher start page</title>
            <para>The default landing page of the Docker image is <link xlink:href="/">localhost:8080</link> and it was built from a
                    <link xlink:href="quickstart.xml?id=intro-jinks#intro-jinks">Jinks
                    profile</link>. Jinks is the new TEI Publisher application manager. The <link xlink:href="/" xlink:show="new">TEI Publisher homepage</link> consists of three different <emphasis role="bold">Jinks profiles</emphasis> and Jinks itself:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tei-publisher/browse.html" xlink:show="new">Documentation &amp; Demo </link> - this article is part of the profile for self-guided learning.
                    </para>
                </listitem>                    
                <listitem>
                    <para>    
                        <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tp-serafin/" xlink:show="new">Serafin</link> - Real-world correspondence edition example
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tp-workbench/">Workbench</link> - Interactive TEI editing
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                    
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>Via the <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/dashboard" xlink:show="new">eXist-db Dashboard</link> you can see the TEI Publisher application manager <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/jinks" xlink:show="new">Jinks</link> itself, all applications created with Jinks, and all other
             eXist-db applications.</para>
        </section>
    </section>
