    <section xml:id="production">
        <title>Server installation</title>
        <subtitle>TEI Publisher in Production Environment</subtitle>
        <para><emphasis>In production</emphasis> means running TEI Publisher on a server available on the internet. It differs significantly from the <link linkend="installation">local installation</link> on your private computer.</para>
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis role="bold">
                            Make sure TEI Publisher runs on a hardened (secured by minimizing vulnerabilities) eXist-db.
                        </emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>You can use community-provided hardened eXist-db images, e.g. <link xlink:href="https://hub.docker.com/layers/duncdrum/existdb/release-nonroot-slim/images/sha256-0957a844af0a9d4b1b246c361956d9f13985b7b4b66e0ebc27736f14eacc2eab" xlink:show="new">duncdrum/existdb:release-nonroot-slim</link> in a Docker Compose setup,
                        create your own images, or install <link xlink:href="http://exist-db.org/exist/apps/doc/basic-installation" xlink:show="new">eXist-db
                            bare metal</link>. In either case please make sure to follow the eXist-db
                        Documentation on <link xlink:href="http://exist-db.org/exist/apps/doc/production_good_practice" xlink:show="new">Production Use - Good Practice</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <important>                            
                            <para>
                            <emphasis role="bold">
                            It is strongly recommended to use a <link xlink:href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proxy_server" xlink:show="new">proxy server
                        </link>in production environments!
                        </emphasis></para>
                        </important>
                    </para>
                    <para>See <link xlink:href="documentation.xml?id=proxy">running behind a
                            proxy</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                    <link xlink:href="https://www.e-editiones.org/pages/get-in-touch/" xlink:show="new">Get in
                        touch</link> in case you or your IT Department are having any security concerns
                    about hosting TEI Publisher or eXist-db. See <link xlink:href="documentation.xml?id=hosting" xlink:show="new">Hosting
                        Options</link> if you'd like to outsource this service.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
    </section>    
